 <section class="homehealth-intro">
  <div class="homehealth-text" data-aos="fade-up">
    <p>
      At Anarcare, we bring Physician ordered quality medical care directly to your home. Certain medical treatments and rehabilitative procedures that once required a hospital visit can now be provided where you’re most comfortable—at your home or wherever you live.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Home health care is more convenient and affordable, while maintaining the standards and effectiveness of medical facilities.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Our goal is to help patients recover from illness or injury, regain independence, and maintain or improve their daily function. Home health care supports your ability to live safely and confidently at home while helping prevent further health decline.
    </p>
    <p>
      Insurance covers home health care services if certain conditions are met. If you have Medicare or other insurance plans, check your plan or contact your provider to understand covered benefits.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>


  <!-- Eligibility -->
<section class="homehealth-section light-pink reverse">
  <div class="section-content">
    <div class="image-side">
      <img src="~/images/home_2.webp" alt="Doctor discussing eligibility" />
    </div>
    <div class="text-side">
      <h3>Eligibility for Home Health Care</h3>
      <p>You may qualify if:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You are under the care of a doctor, NP, or PA with a reviewed care plan.</li>
        <li>Your provider certifies the need for intermittent skilled nursing care, PT, OT, or speech therapy.</li>
        <li>You are homebound (need help to leave home or leaving home is not recommended).</li>
        <li>The home health agency is Medicare-certified.</li>
        <li>You had a recent face-to-face visit with your provider for this need.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


  <!-- Skilled Nursing -->
 <section class="homehealth-section red-bg">
  <div class="section-content">
    <div class="image-side">
      <img src="~/images/home_3_1.webp" alt="Skilled Nursing" />
    </div>
    <div class="text-side">
      <h3>Covered services include:<br><strong>Skilled Nursing Care</strong></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Services that require the expertise of a registered nurse (RN) or licensed practical nurse (LPN) under supervision of RN.</li>
        <li>A nurse can provide IV therapy, injections, wound care, tube feedings, diabetes and medication management per Physician Orders.</li>
        <li>Home Health Services must be part-time or intermittent:
          <ul>
            <li>Less than 8 hours per day</li>
            <li>28 or fewer hours per week (up to 35 hours in special cases)</li>
            <li><em>Routine services like blood draws alone are not covered</em></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


  <!-- Therapy Services -->
<section class="homehealth-section gray reverse">
  <div class="section-content reverse">
    <div class="image-side">
